Note:
Comprehensive Test Suite for Memory Layout Module

Tests all functionality of the memory layout modeling, analysis, and optimization system including:
- Memory models (flat, segmented, virtual) with comprehensive struct layout computation
- Alignment and padding analysis with optimization recommendations
- Struct and array layout computation with various data types
- Cache line optimization and false sharing detection with severity analysis
- Introspection and validation APIs for layout verification
- AI/agent-friendly layout analysis and reporting
- Production-ready robustness and extensibility testing
- Performance benchmarks for layout computation and analysis
:End Note

Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/memory/memory_layout" as MemoryLayout
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/utilities/common" as Common

Note: Test Configuration Constants
Let TEST_CACHE_LINE_SIZE be 64
Let TEST_STRUCT_ALIGNMENT be 8
Let TEST_MAX_FIELD_COUNT be 20
Let TEST_PADDING_THRESHOLD be 0.5

Note: Test Result Tracking
Let test_results be Dictionary[String, Boolean] containing
Let test_count be 0
Let passed_count be 0
Let failed_count be 0

Note: Helper Functions for Testing

Process called "run_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Function returns Boolean:
    Set test_count to test_count plus 1
    
    Try:
        Display message "Running test: " plus test_name
        Let result be test_function()
        
        If result:
            Set passed_count to passed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to true
            Display message "  ✓ PASS: " plus test_name
        Otherwise:
            Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to false
            Display message "  ✗ FAIL: " plus test_name
            
        Return result
        
    Catch error:
        Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
        Set test_results[test_name] to false
        Display message "  ✗ ERROR: " plus test_name plus " - " plus convert_to_string with value as error
        Return false

Process called "assert_equals" that takes actual as Any and expected as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is equal to expected:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected: " plus convert_to_string with value as expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus convert_to_string with value as actual
        Return false

Process called "assert_not_none" that takes value as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If value is not None:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message plus " - value is None"
        Return false

Process called "assert_true" that takes value as Boolean and message as String returns Boolean:
    If value is true:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message plus " - expected true, got false"
        Return false

Process called "assert_false" that takes value as Boolean and message as String returns Boolean:
    If value is false:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message plus " - expected false, got true"
        Return false

Process called "assert_greater_than" that takes actual as Number and expected as Number and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is greater than expected:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected > " plus convert_to_string with value as expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus convert_to_string with value as actual
        Return false

Process called "assert_less_than" that takes actual as Number and expected as Number and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is less than expected:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected < " plus convert_to_string with value as expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus convert_to_string with value as actual
        Return false

Process called "assert_less_than_or_equal" that takes actual as Number and expected as Number and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is less than or equal to expected:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected <= " plus convert_to_string with value as expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus convert_to_string with value as actual
        Return false

Process called "create_test_field" that takes name as String and size as Integer and alignment as Integer returns MemoryLayout.LayoutField:
    Note: Creates a test layout field with specified parameters
    Return MemoryLayout.LayoutField with:
        name as name
        offset as 0
        size as size
        alignment as alignment
        padding as 0
        metadata as dictionary containing
            "test_field" as true
            "created_at" as Common.get_current_timestamp

Process called "create_simple_struct_fields" returns List[MemoryLayout.LayoutField]:
    Note: Creates a simple struct with basic data types
    Let fields be list containing
    
    Note: char field (1 byte, 1-byte aligned)
    Add create_test_field with name as "char_field" and size as 1 and alignment as 1 to fields
    
    Note: int field (4 bytes, 4-byte aligned)
    Add create_test_field with name as "int_field" and size as 4 and alignment as 4 to fields
    
    Note: double field (8 bytes, 8-byte aligned)
    Add create_test_field with name as "double_field" and size as 8 and alignment as 8 to fields
    
    Note: short field (2 bytes, 2-byte aligned)
    Add create_test_field with name as "short_field" and size as 2 and alignment as 2 to fields
    
    Return fields

Process called "create_complex_struct_fields" returns List[MemoryLayout.LayoutField]:
    Note: Creates a complex struct with various alignment requirements
    Let fields be list containing
    
    Note: Various sized fields for complex layout testing
    Add create_test_field with name as "byte_field" and size as 1 and alignment as 1 to fields
    Add create_test_field with name as "word_field" and size as 2 and alignment as 2 to fields
    Add create_test_field with name as "dword_field" and size as 4 and alignment as 4 to fields
    Add create_test_field with name as "qword_field" and size as 8 and alignment as 8 to fields
    Add create_test_field with name as "array_field" and size as 12 and alignment as 4 to fields
    Add create_test_field with name as "pointer_field" and size as 8 and alignment as 8 to fields
    Add create_test_field with name as "bool_field" and size as 1 and alignment as 1 to fields
    Add create_test_field with name as "float_field" and size as 4 and alignment as 4 to fields
    
    Return fields

Process called "create_false_sharing_fields" returns List[MemoryLayout.LayoutField]:
    Note: Creates fields that will likely cause false sharing
    Let fields be list containing
    
    Note: Small fields that will pack into same cache line
    For i from 0 to 15:
        Let field_name be "small_field_" plus convert_to_string with value as i
        Add create_test_field with name as field_name and size as 4 and alignment as 4 to fields
    
    Return fields

Note: Core Layout Computation Tests

Process called "test_basic_struct_layout_computation":
    Note: Tests basic struct layout computation with simple fields
    Let fields be create_simple_struct_fields
    Let layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "flat"
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as layout and message as "Layout should be computed"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as layout.model and expected as "flat" and message as "Layout model should match"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as layout.size and expected as 0 and message as "Layout size should be positive"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as layout.alignment and expected as 0 and message as "Layout alignment should be positive"
    Let result5 be assert_equals with actual as length of layout.fields and expected as 4 and message as "Should have all fields"
    Let result6 be assert_not_none with value as layout.cache_lines and message as "Cache lines should be analyzed"
    
    Note: Verify fields are properly aligned
    For each field in layout.fields:
        Let aligned_properly be (field.offset modulo field.alignment) is equal to 0
        If not aligned_properly:
            Display message "  Field " plus field.name plus " is not properly aligned"
            Return false
    
    Let result7 be true
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6 and result7

Process called "test_complex_struct_layout_computation":
    Note: Tests complex struct layout with various alignment requirements
    Let fields be create_complex_struct_fields
    Let layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "segmented"
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as layout and message as "Complex layout should be computed"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as layout.model and expected as "segmented" and message as "Layout model should match"
    Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as length of layout.fields and expected as 8 and message as "Should have all complex fields"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as layout.size and expected as 20 and message as "Complex layout should have substantial size"
    
    Note: Verify struct alignment matches largest field alignment
    Let max_field_alignment be 0
    For each field in layout.fields:
        If field.alignment is greater than max_field_alignment:
            Set max_field_alignment to field.alignment
    
    Let result5 be assert_equals with actual as layout.alignment and expected as max_field_alignment and message as "Struct alignment should match largest field"
    
    Note: Verify no fields overlap
    For i from 0 to (length of layout.fields minus 2):
        Let current_field be layout.fields[i]
        Let next_field be layout.fields[i plus 1]
        Let current_end be current_field.offset plus current_field.size
        Let overlap_check be current_end is less than or equal to next_field.offset
        If not overlap_check:
            Display message "  Fields overlap: " plus current_field.name plus " and " plus next_field.name
            Return false
    
    Let result6 be true
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6

Process called "test_alignment_and_padding_calculation":
    Note: Tests alignment and padding calculations
    Let fields be create_simple_struct_fields
    Let layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "flat"
    
    Note: Test align_up function
    Let align_4_test be MemoryLayout.align_up with value as 5 and alignment as 4
    Let result1 be assert_equals with actual as align_4_test and expected as 8 and message as "align_up(5, 4) should be 8"
    
    Let align_8_test be MemoryLayout.align_up with value as 9 and alignment as 8
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as align_8_test and expected as 16 and message as "align_up(9, 8) should be 16"
    
    Note: Test align_down function
    Let align_down_4_test be MemoryLayout.align_down with value as 7 and alignment as 4
    Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as align_down_4_test and expected as 4 and message as "align_down(7, 4) should be 4"
    
    Note: Test padding calculation
    Let padding_test be MemoryLayout.calculate_padding with current_offset as 5 and alignment as 4
    Let result4 be assert_equals with actual as padding_test and expected as 3 and message as "Padding for offset 5 with alignment 4 should be 3"
    
    Note: Test total padding calculation
    Let total_padding be MemoryLayout.calculate_total_padding with fields as layout.fields
    Let result5 be assert_greater_than with actual as total_padding and expected as -1 and message as "Total padding should be non-negative"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5

Process called "test_cache_line_analysis":
    Note: Tests cache line analysis and detection
    Let fields be create_simple_struct_fields
    Let layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "flat"
    Let cache_lines be MemoryLayout.analyze_cache_lines with layout as layout and cache_line_size as TEST_CACHE_LINE_SIZE
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as cache_lines and message as "Cache lines should be analyzed"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of cache_lines and expected as 0 and message as "Should have cache lines"
    
    Note: Verify cache line structure
    For each cache_line in cache_lines:
        Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as cache_line.end minus cache_line.start and expected as TEST_CACHE_LINE_SIZE minus 1 and message as "Cache line size should be correct"
        Let result4 be assert_equals with actual as cache_line.start and expected as cache_line.index multiplied by TEST_CACHE_LINE_SIZE and message as "Cache line start should be aligned"
        If not (result3 and result4):
            Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "test_false_sharing_detection":
    Note: Tests false sharing detection and reporting
    Let fields be create_false_sharing_fields
    Let layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "flat"
    
    Note: Detect false sharing
    Let false_sharing_reports be MemoryLayout.detect_false_sharing with layout as layout
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as false_sharing_reports and message as "False sharing reports should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of false_sharing_reports and expected as 0 and message as "Should detect false sharing in packed fields"
    
    Note: Verify false sharing report structure
    If length of false_sharing_reports is greater than 0:
        Let first_report be false_sharing_reports[0]
        Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as first_report.cache_line_index and message as "Report should have cache line index"
        Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of first_report.affected_fields and expected as 1 and message as "Report should have affected fields"
        Let result5 be assert_not_none with value as first_report.severity and message as "Report should have severity"
        Let result6 be assert_not_none with value as first_report.suggestions and message as "Report should have suggestions"
        Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_layout_validation":
    Note: Tests layout validation with various scenarios
    Let valid_fields be create_simple_struct_fields
    Let valid_layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as valid_fields and model as "flat"
    
    Note: Test valid layout
    Let valid_result be MemoryLayout.validate_layout with layout as valid_layout
    Let result1 be assert_true with value as valid_result and message as "Valid layout should pass validation"
    
    Note: Test layout with false sharing
    Let false_sharing_fields be create_false_sharing_fields
    Let false_sharing_layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as false_sharing_fields and model as "flat"
    Let false_sharing_result be MemoryLayout.validate_layout with layout as false_sharing_layout
    Let result2 be assert_false with value as false_sharing_result and message as "Layout with false sharing should fail validation"
    
    Note: Create a layout with excessive padding (manually constructed for testing)
    Let padded_layout be MemoryLayout.MemoryLayout with:
        model as "test"
        alignment as 8
        padding as 100
        size as 200
        fields as list containing create_test_field with name as "small" and size as 4 and alignment as 4
        cache_lines as list containing
        metadata as dictionary containing
    
    Let padded_result be MemoryLayout.validate_layout with layout as padded_layout
    Let result3 be assert_false with value as padded_result and message as "Layout with excessive padding should fail validation"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Advanced Analysis Tests

Process called "test_false_sharing_severity_analysis":
    Note: Tests false sharing severity calculation
    Let fields be create_false_sharing_fields
    Let layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "flat"
    Let reports be MemoryLayout.detect_false_sharing with layout as layout
    
    Let result1 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of reports and expected as 0 and message as "Should have false sharing reports"
    
    Note: Test severity levels
    If length of reports is greater than 0:
        Let first_report be reports[0]
        Let severity_valid be (first_report.severity is equal to "low") or (first_report.severity is equal to "medium") or (first_report.severity is equal to "high") or (first_report.severity is equal to "critical")
        Let result2 be assert_true with value as severity_valid and message as "Severity should be valid level"
        
        Note: Test severity correlation with field count
        Let field_count be length of first_report.affected_fields
        If field_count is greater than 4:
            Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as first_report.severity and expected as "critical" and message as "High field count should be critical severity"
            Return result1 and result2 and result3
        
        Return result1 and result2
    
    Return result1

Process called "test_optimization_suggestions":
    Note: Tests optimization suggestion generation
    Let fields be create_false_sharing_fields
    Let layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "flat"
    Let reports be MemoryLayout.detect_false_sharing with layout as layout
    
    Let result1 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of reports and expected as 0 and message as "Should have reports for suggestions test"
    
    If length of reports is greater than 0:
        Let first_report be reports[0]
        Let result2 be assert_not_none with value as first_report.suggestions and message as "Report should have suggestions"
        Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of first_report.suggestions and expected as 0 and message as "Should have at least one suggestion"
        
        Note: Verify suggestions are actionable strings
        For each suggestion in first_report.suggestions:
            If suggestion is None or length of suggestion is equal to 0:
                Display message "  Empty suggestion found"
                Return false
        
        Let result4 be true
        Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4
    
    Return result1

Process called "test_memory_model_variations":
    Note: Tests different memory models
    Let fields be create_simple_struct_fields
    
    Note: Test flat memory model
    Let flat_layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "flat"
    Let result1 be assert_equals with actual as flat_layout.model and expected as "flat" and message as "Flat model should be set"
    
    Note: Test segmented memory model
    Let segmented_layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "segmented"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as segmented_layout.model and expected as "segmented" and message as "Segmented model should be set"
    
    Note: Test virtual memory model
    Let virtual_layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "virtual"
    Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as virtual_layout.model and expected as "virtual" and message as "Virtual model should be set"
    
    Note: All models should produce valid layouts
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as flat_layout.size and expected as 0 and message as "Flat layout should have positive size"
    Let result5 be assert_greater_than with actual as segmented_layout.size and expected as 0 and message as "Segmented layout should have positive size"
    Let result6 be assert_greater_than with actual as virtual_layout.size and expected as 0 and message as "Virtual layout should have positive size"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6

Process called "test_cache_line_optimization":
    Note: Tests cache line optimization recommendations
    Let fields be create_complex_struct_fields
    Let layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "flat"
    Let cache_lines be MemoryLayout.analyze_cache_lines with layout as layout and cache_line_size as TEST_CACHE_LINE_SIZE
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as cache_lines and message as "Cache line analysis should work"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of cache_lines and expected as 0 and message as "Should have cache lines for complex struct"
    
    Note: Check cache line utilization
    Let total_fields be 0
    For each cache_line in cache_lines:
        Set total_fields to total_fields plus (length of cache_line.fields)
    
    Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as total_fields and expected as length of layout.fields and message as "All fields should be in cache lines"
    
    Note: Check for optimal packing (no empty cache lines between used ones)
    Let empty_cache_lines be 0
    For each cache_line in cache_lines:
        If length of cache_line.fields is equal to 0:
            Set empty_cache_lines to empty_cache_lines plus 1
    
    Let result4 be assert_less_than_or_equal with actual as empty_cache_lines and expected as 1 and message as "Should have minimal empty cache lines"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Note: Performance and Stress Tests

Process called "test_large_struct_layout_performance":
    Note: Tests performance with large structs
    Let large_fields be list containing
    
    Note: Create a large struct with many fields
    For i from 0 to 99:
        Let field_name be "field_" plus convert_to_string with value as i
        Let field_size be (i modulo 8) plus 1
        Let field_alignment be field_size
        Add create_test_field with name as field_name and size as field_size and alignment as field_alignment to large_fields
    
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_timestamp
    Let large_layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as large_fields and model as "flat"
    Let end_time be Common.get_current_timestamp
    Let computation_time be end_time minus start_time
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as large_layout and message as "Large struct layout should be computed"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as length of large_layout.fields and expected as 100 and message as "Should have all fields"
    Let result3 be assert_less_than with actual as computation_time and expected as 5000 and message as "Large struct computation should be fast (< 5s)"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_cache_line_analysis_performance":
    Note: Tests performance of cache line analysis
    Let fields be create_complex_struct_fields
    Let layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "flat"
    
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_timestamp
    Let cache_lines be MemoryLayout.analyze_cache_lines with layout as layout and cache_line_size as TEST_CACHE_LINE_SIZE
    Let end_time be Common.get_current_timestamp
    Let analysis_time be end_time minus start_time
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as cache_lines and message as "Cache line analysis should complete"
    Let result2 be assert_less_than with actual as analysis_time and expected as 1000 and message as "Cache line analysis should be fast (< 1s)"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_false_sharing_detection_performance":
    Note: Tests performance of false sharing detection
    Let fields be create_false_sharing_fields
    Let layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "flat"
    
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_timestamp
    Let reports be MemoryLayout.detect_false_sharing with layout as layout
    Let end_time be Common.get_current_timestamp
    Let detection_time be end_time minus start_time
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as reports and message as "False sharing detection should complete"
    Let result2 be assert_less_than with actual as detection_time and expected as 2000 and message as "False sharing detection should be fast (< 2s)"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_validation_performance":
    Note: Tests performance of layout validation
    Let fields be create_complex_struct_fields
    Let layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "flat"
    
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_timestamp
    Let validation_result be MemoryLayout.validate_layout with layout as layout
    Let end_time be Common.get_current_timestamp
    Let validation_time be end_time minus start_time
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as validation_result and message as "Validation should complete"
    Let result2 be assert_less_than with actual as validation_time and expected as 500 and message as "Validation should be very fast (< 0.5s)"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: AI/Agent Integration Tests

Process called "test_ai_layout_analysis_api":
    Note: Tests AI-friendly layout analysis APIs
    Let fields be create_complex_struct_fields
    Let layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "flat"
    
    Note: Generate AI-friendly layout report
    Let ai_report be dictionary containing
        "layout_model" as layout.model
        "total_size" as layout.size
        "alignment" as layout.alignment
        "field_count" as length of layout.fields
        "cache_line_count" as length of layout.cache_lines
        "total_padding" as layout.metadata["total_padding"]
        "padding_ratio" as (layout.metadata["total_padding"] as Float) divided by (layout.size as Float)
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as ai_report and message as "AI report should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as ai_report["total_size"] and expected as 0 and message as "AI report should have valid size"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as ai_report["field_count"] and expected as 0 and message as "AI report should have field count"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as ai_report["padding_ratio"] and expected as 0.0 and message as "AI report should have padding ratio"
    
    Note: Test false sharing analysis for AI
    Let false_sharing_reports be MemoryLayout.detect_false_sharing with layout as layout
    Let ai_false_sharing_summary be dictionary containing
        "total_reports" as length of false_sharing_reports
        "critical_issues" as count_reports_by_severity with reports as false_sharing_reports and severity as "critical"
        "high_issues" as count_reports_by_severity with reports as false_sharing_reports and severity as "high"
        "optimization_needed" as (length of false_sharing_reports) is greater than 0
    
    Let result5 be assert_not_none with value as ai_false_sharing_summary and message as "AI false sharing summary should be generated"
    Let result6 be assert_greater_than with actual as ai_false_sharing_summary["total_reports"] and expected as -1 and message as "AI summary should have report count"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6

Process called "test_agent_optimization_recommendations":
    Note: Tests agent-driven optimization recommendations
    Let fields be create_false_sharing_fields
    Let layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "flat"
    Let false_sharing_reports be MemoryLayout.detect_false_sharing with layout as layout
    
    Note: Generate agent-friendly optimization recommendations
    Let optimization_recommendations be list containing
    For each report in false_sharing_reports:
        Let recommendation be dictionary containing
            "issue_type" as "false_sharing"
            "severity" as report.severity
            "affected_cache_line" as report.cache_line_index
            "affected_fields" as report.affected_fields
            "recommendations" as report.suggestions
            "priority" as calculate_priority_from_severity with severity as report.severity
        Add recommendation to optimization_recommendations
    
    Let result1 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of optimization_recommendations and expected as 0 and message as "Should have optimization recommendations"
    
    If length of optimization_recommendations is greater than 0:
        Let first_recommendation be optimization_recommendations[0]
        Let result2 be assert_not_none with value as first_recommendation["issue_type"] and message as "Recommendation should have issue type"
        Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as first_recommendation["severity"] and message as "Recommendation should have severity"
        Let result4 be assert_not_none with value as first_recommendation["priority"] and message as "Recommendation should have priority"
        Let result5 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of first_recommendation["recommendations"] and expected as 0 and message as "Should have actionable recommendations"
        Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5
    
    Return result1

Note: Production Readiness Tests

Process called "test_enterprise_layout_analysis":
    Note: Tests enterprise-grade layout analysis features
    Let fields be create_complex_struct_fields
    Let layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "flat"
    
    Note: Generate comprehensive enterprise report
    Let enterprise_report be dictionary containing
        "analysis_timestamp" as Common.get_current_timestamp
        "layout_summary" as dictionary containing
            "model" as layout.model
            "total_size_bytes" as layout.size
            "alignment_bytes" as layout.alignment
            "field_count" as length of layout.fields
            "padding_bytes" as layout.metadata["total_padding"]
        "performance_analysis" as dictionary containing
            "cache_line_utilization" as calculate_cache_line_utilization with layout as layout
            "false_sharing_risk" as assess_false_sharing_risk with layout as layout
            "memory_efficiency" as calculate_memory_efficiency with layout as layout
        "recommendations" as generate_enterprise_recommendations with layout as layout
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as enterprise_report and message as "Enterprise report should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_not_none with value as enterprise_report["analysis_timestamp"] and message as "Report should have timestamp"
    Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as enterprise_report["layout_summary"] and message as "Report should have layout summary"
    Let result4 be assert_not_none with value as enterprise_report["performance_analysis"] and message as "Report should have performance analysis"
    Let result5 be assert_not_none with value as enterprise_report["recommendations"] and message as "Report should have recommendations"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5

Process called "test_production_safety_validation":
    Note: Tests production safety validation
    Let fields be create_simple_struct_fields
    Let layout be MemoryLayout.compute_struct_layout with fields as fields and model as "flat"
    
    Note: Test production safety checks
    Let safety_checks be dictionary containing
        "alignment_valid" as validate_field_alignment with layout as layout
        "size_reasonable" as validate_size_reasonable with layout as layout
        "no_overlaps" as validate_no_field_overlaps with layout as layout
        "cache_friendly" as validate_cache_friendliness with layout as layout
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with value as safety_checks["alignment_valid"] and message as "Field alignment should be valid"
    Let result2 be assert_true with value as safety_checks["size_reasonable"] and message as "Size should be reasonable"
    Let result3 be assert_true with value as safety_checks["no_overlaps"] and message as "Fields should not overlap"
    Let result4 be assert_not_none with value as safety_checks["cache_friendly"] and message as "Cache friendliness should be assessed"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Note: Helper Functions for Testing

Process called "count_reports_by_severity" that takes reports as List[MemoryLayout.FalseSharingReport] and severity as String returns Integer:
    Note: Counts false sharing reports by severity level
    Let count be 0
    For each report in reports:
        If report.severity is equal to severity:
            Set count to count plus 1
    Return count

Process called "calculate_priority_from_severity" that takes severity as String returns String:
    Note: Calculates priority from severity level
    If severity is equal to "critical":
        Return "immediate"
    If severity is equal to "high":
        Return "urgent"
    If severity is equal to "medium":
        Return "normal"
    Otherwise:
        Return "low"

Process called "calculate_cache_line_utilization" that takes layout as MemoryLayout.MemoryLayout returns Float:
    Note: Calculates cache line utilization percentage
    Let used_cache_lines be 0
    For each cache_line in layout.cache_lines:
        If length of cache_line.fields is greater than 0:
            Set used_cache_lines to used_cache_lines plus 1
    
    If length of layout.cache_lines is greater than 0:
        Return (used_cache_lines as Float) divided by (length of layout.cache_lines as Float)
    Otherwise:
        Return 0.0

Process called "assess_false_sharing_risk" that takes layout as MemoryLayout.MemoryLayout returns String:
    Note: Assesses false sharing risk level
    Let false_sharing_count be MemoryLayout.count_false_sharing with cache_lines as layout.cache_lines
    If false_sharing_count is greater than 3:
        Return "high"
    If false_sharing_count is greater than 1:
        Return "medium"
    If false_sharing_count is greater than 0:
        Return "low"
    Otherwise:
        Return "none"

Process called "calculate_memory_efficiency" that takes layout as MemoryLayout.MemoryLayout returns Float:
    Note: Calculates memory efficiency as ratio of useful data to total size
    Let total_field_size be 0
    For each field in layout.fields:
        Set total_field_size to total_field_size plus field.size
    
    If layout.size is greater than 0:
        Return (total_field_size as Float) divided by (layout.size as Float)
    Otherwise:
        Return 0.0

Process called "generate_enterprise_recommendations" that takes layout as MemoryLayout.MemoryLayout returns List[String]:
    Note: Generates enterprise-level optimization recommendations
    Let recommendations be list containing
    
    Let efficiency be calculate_memory_efficiency with layout as layout
    If efficiency is less than 0.7:
        Add "Consider reordering fields to reduce padding overhead" to recommendations
    
    Let false_sharing_risk be assess_false_sharing_risk with layout as layout
    If false_sharing_risk is not equal to "none":
        Add "Review field grouping to minimize false sharing" to recommendations
    
    Let cache_utilization be calculate_cache_line_utilization with layout as layout
    If cache_utilization is less than 0.8:
        Add "Optimize field layout for better cache line utilization" to recommendations
    
    If length of recommendations is equal to 0:
        Add "Layout is well-optimized for current requirements" to recommendations
    
    Return recommendations

Process called "validate_field_alignment" that takes layout as MemoryLayout.MemoryLayout returns Boolean:
    Note: Validates that all fields are properly aligned
    For each field in layout.fields:
        If field.offset modulo field.alignment is not equal to 0:
            Return false
    Return true

Process called "validate_size_reasonable" that takes layout as MemoryLayout.MemoryLayout returns Boolean:
    Note: Validates that layout size is reasonable
    Return layout.size is greater than 0 and layout.size is less than 1048576

Process called "validate_no_field_overlaps" that takes layout as MemoryLayout.MemoryLayout returns Boolean:
    Note: Validates that fields do not overlap
    For i from 0 to (length of layout.fields minus 2):
        Let current_field be layout.fields[i]
        Let next_field be layout.fields[i plus 1]
        Let current_end be current_field.offset plus current_field.size
        If current_end is greater than next_field.offset:
            Return false
    Return true

Process called "validate_cache_friendliness" that takes layout as MemoryLayout.MemoryLayout returns Boolean:
    Note: Validates cache-friendly layout
    Let false_sharing_count be MemoryLayout.count_false_sharing with cache_lines as layout.cache_lines
    Return false_sharing_count is less than 3

Process called "convert_to_string" that takes value as Any returns String:
    Note: Converts any value to string representation
    Return "test_value"

Note: Main Test Execution

